title: For Sale:  Lyman Plains Pistol
postcontent: FOR SALE: Used, in excellent condition:  a .50 caliber single shot (percussion), Lyman Plains Pistol. Pistol features walnut stock, 9” barrel with a 1 in 30” twist, brass trigger guard and wooden ramrod. This pistol would make an ideal ‘camp’ gun where the authorities might otherwise frown upon or outright arrest you for having a modern arm, and the caliber is such that it should be able to handle most any camp emergency. This is also a neat gun to take to the club or local shooting range where a couple of rounds fired off will fill the shooting  ports with smoke and have all the curious gathering around your point for a look see. Pistol comes with in-line capper, short ball starter, belt hook, and loading instructions. This pistol will take either a .490 round ball with a .010 to .015 patch or a .495 round ball with a .010 to .005 patch. Nipple is a common 6mm x .75, as found on most Pietta percussion revolvers. Cap size #11 is called for, but depending on the maker some # 10’s will fire off a charge as well. All black powder substitutes {Pyrodex/Triple Seven} can be used in this gun as well as black powder – this includes both pistol and rifle grade [FFFg / FFg] powders. While modern loading specs call for FFFg powder, FFg grade was used in mostly all black powder loads back in the day – this includes black powder cartridges. Asking $200.00 - FIRM - for this piece and no trades; I have everything I want - shipping and insurance costs included. Please note – ridiculously low offers will go unanswered. I accept for payment:  money orders, bank checks, and verifiable personal checks. I will answer your e-mail inquiries, but please be patient – I don’t live on my computer and my time on such varies from day to day. Please be sure that you really want this piece before you jerk me around for three days and then decide to crawfish out of the deal. Thanks for stopping by and looking.

title: Want To Buy:  Looking for quailty handgun
postcontent:
Due to the overwhelming amount of uninformed people who feel the need to E-mail me and pretend to be an expert on the laws, I must add this important information.
IT IS COMPLETELY LEGAL TO BUY A HANDGUN THROUGH A PRIVATE SALE AT THE AGE OF 18. YOU MUST BE 21 TO BUY THROUGH AN FFL, BUT 18 FOR PRIVATE SALES.     Now that that's over with, on to my ad

I am an 18 year old college student looking to buy a nice quality handgun preferably in 9mm or 45. I'm looking for something I can keep in my glove box or beside my bed for the next three years and then use as a carry piece. I may be interested in a revolver, but semi-auto is preferred. I'd also like it to be polymer framed, and ambidextrous as I shoot lefty, but it doesn't have to be. I've been dealing with it for years

I'd like to stay in the $300~ range or am willing to trade a couple month old Mossberg 535 12 gauge at $450 trade value. Camo, pistol grip, multi-position stock, and fiber-optic sights. Just shot it for the first time this weekend and it's flawless. 5+1 capacity.
If trading, I'd like to get a nice handgun and another (cheap) 12 or 20 gauge for home defense use. 
I also have some fishing poles that I wouldn't mind trading off. I love fishing, just don't need this many poles. 
I may add cash for the right multi gun trade.

Calibers considered: 380, 38 special, 357, 9mm, 40, 45. 
Would like to stick with the big manufacturers: S&W, Ruger, Glock, Taurus, Bersa, etc. but most others considered.
Would also consider a Kel-Tec in the $250 range.

All offers considered, the worst I can say is no thank you.

I may also be interested in a cheap (~$100) 22 caliber handgun to plink with on the weekends/camping trips. Semi-auto, revolver, it doesn't matter. Not too picky with this one as long as it shoots. No Jimenez, Jennings, Bryco, Raven or HiPoints!

Send me an E-mail with your offer and we'll go from there.

postcontent:
THIS GUN WAS MADE BEFORE 1899 AND IS CONSIDERED AN ANTIQUE, THEREFORE IS NOT CONSIDERED A FIREARM. CHECK YOU LOCAL LAWS AND LISTINGS.


This is a 5-shot top break .32 revolver. The timing is perfect. It is in excellent condition, there is no rust on it, barely any patina. It looks like a large gun but it is actually very small and compact, no longer than most cell phones and has a smaller profile than most wheel guns. The barrel is about 3 inches long.

Despite being an antique, this gun is actually very modular.

You could shoot .32 ACP out of it so long as it was lead ammo, and not FMJ.

title: For Sale:  Rossi 851 .38 Special 4" Excellent Plus Condition
postcontent: Offered is my Stainless Steel Rossi 851 .38 Special with 4" ventilated rib barrel in Like New Condition. I have collected handguns imported by InterArms of Alexandria VA for over 30 years and now I soon to retire and relocate and am selling the last of my collection. This is a modern .38 Special made entirely of Stainless Steel and is suitable for for defensive and/or recreational use, it is also collectible. It has adjustable sights, beautiful Brazilian hardwood grips, and it holds 6 rounds of .38 Special ammo. This revolver appears to have been been fired very little. I have never fired it, it's a safe queen that sits on a carpeted shelf in my climatically controlled safe, there is not a mark on it anywhere that I can see and it looks like it left the factory yesterday. Mechanical function is perfect; the cylinder locks and unlocks properly and there is no cylinder play or slop, trigger pull is very nice with no creep or stacking, the bore is perfect with crisp and sharp lands and grooves and the stainless steel finish is a nice as any I've ever seen on any revolver. There is not another revolver on the market today with all the positive attributes this revolver has, the 4" barrel and ventilated rib are particular desirable. Will meet buyer at a store front FFL dealer for a MSP compliant transfer, I use a shop in Charles County and one in southern Prince George's county and they are both a pleasure to work with, I will consider your dealer if you don't want to use either of these guys but I'm not interested in driving any further north than Bowie, MD. I won't rule out going thru an local MSP barracks but I have found them to be less than accommodating in doing transfers between private individuals. Once we meet at the dealer, you pay me in full in cash, we both do the MSP paperwork, then my part of the transaction is complete, buyer pays FFL and MSP fees, and must have Maryland HQL. I will ship out of state (where legal) to your FFL if you pay for insured shipping. Not interested in trades of any sort.

postcontent: I have a #'s matching rifle in excellent shape,Brigt and shinny bore, good rifling, no rust. The barrel, beech, bolt,bayonet holder, and arsenal renumbered stock are #'s matching.Chambered in 8X56, I've been researching these rifles for a while, and just that description has brought up to $500 for some of these. Average condition and nonmatching #'s from $300 & up. But mine has something I've never seen mentioned and as such am unsure of the value. The stock has been stamped with a Nazi eagle crest w/SS and under it reads WaA2. I  think it's an Abbreviation for Wehrmacht Division A2. The Gestopo, under Heinrich Muller had internal departments asigned to investigate and act upon certain groups they were A1 Communists,A2 Counter Sabotage,A3 Reactionaries and Liberals, & A4 Assassinations. There were also departments B,C,D, & E. Dept B was Sects and churches, B1 Catholics, B2 Protestants,B3 Freemasons and B4 Jews. If you want to know more I found this info on Wikipedia under the term Gestopo. It also said the Gestopo or Hitlers Secret Police used a number of these exact rifles, & I believe this to be one of those.it's in too good of shape to have seen any time in the trenches. It's 39" long. Anyone with any info they want to share drop me a line and I'll email you my phone # As far as price goes? Make me an offer...... P.S. I'll try to get some better pics on here, the glare off the stock makes it impossible to see any thing but the Eagle in the crest, but the SS is bright and clear in person....
